<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="644" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Powell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-09"><hi rend="italic">September 9,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Powell states that it is reported that Admiral Killick and two of
                            his officers went down with the <hi rend="italic">Crête.</hi>)</p>
